1
00:01:30,790 --> 00:01:34,726
Hello?
Hello?

2
00:01:51,044 --> 00:01:52,978
Christ.

3
00:02:01,254 --> 00:02:02,619
Help!

4
00:02:02,655 --> 00:02:05,453
Over here!

5
00:02:05,492 --> 00:02:09,292
Help!

6
00:02:13,366 --> 00:02:15,459
I couldn't find
any of you.

7
00:02:15,502 --> 00:02:17,129
How far did we drift?

8
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:19,104
It was about
a kilometer maybe.

9
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:20,572
That's some
freaky pull.

10
00:02:20,607 --> 00:02:24,634
You couldn't see anything,
just a load of bubbles.

11
00:02:24,677 --> 00:02:26,440
I reckon he probably
got drunk

12
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:29,539
- and fell asleep on his lilo.
- We're too far out.

13
00:02:30,617 --> 00:02:33,415
Jesus!

14
00:02:48,568 --> 00:02:51,128
Christ.

15
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:01,973
We've come too far down.
We must have.

16
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:04,006
That's the hotel.

17
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:10,550
John, John!

18
00:03:17,964 --> 00:03:19,932
Martha, where are you?

19
00:03:19,966 --> 00:03:22,264
Hurry up, there may
be another wave.

20
00:03:23,336 --> 00:03:25,133
No no no!

21
00:03:25,171 --> 00:03:28,197
Wait! Ian!

22
00:03:36,616 --> 00:03:40,582
John!

23
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:44,147
Dad, Dad!

24
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:45,919
Ian!

25
00:03:45,959 --> 00:03:48,154
- Dad!
- John!

26
00:03:48,194 --> 00:03:50,094
Martha!

27
00:03:54,968 --> 00:03:56,959
Ian!

28
00:03:58,504 --> 00:04:02,406
Oh my God.
Martha... Ian!

29
00:04:56,329 --> 00:04:59,059
Daddy-- Daddy.

30
00:05:00,266 --> 00:05:02,257
Hey, you.

31
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:06,170
- You forgot to post the paychecks.
- Oh no, I did it today.

32
00:05:06,205 --> 00:05:08,196
Don't worry.
Look at that.

33
00:05:08,241 --> 00:05:10,573
What do you think, sweetheart?
Look at that.

34
00:05:10,610 --> 00:05:12,407
What do you think, baby?

35
00:05:12,445 --> 00:05:15,107
Listen, take her.
I'm just going to check in.

36
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,446
Right.

37
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:20,941
What's first?
What are we doing first?

38
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:22,921
- Swimming.
- Swimming.

39
00:05:25,224 --> 00:05:27,215
You have the passports,
darling?

40
00:05:29,395 --> 00:05:30,862
Stop it.

41
00:05:30,897 --> 00:05:33,422
Adam, help your brother.

42
00:05:33,466 --> 00:05:35,627
Sa-wat dee kha.

43
00:05:35,668 --> 00:05:36,930
Excuse me,
I was about to--

44
00:05:36,969 --> 00:05:38,129
Uh...

45
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:41,436
That's fine.
Go ahead.

46
00:05:41,474 --> 00:05:42,907
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

47
00:05:42,942 --> 00:05:44,910
Merry Christmas.

48
00:05:44,944 --> 00:05:46,673
- Carters.
- Yes, thank you.

49
00:05:48,348 --> 00:05:51,317
- Don't embarrass me.
- Chill, Mom.

50
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:53,945
Come on,
bring the bags.

51
00:06:05,264 --> 00:06:07,391
Hi!

52
00:06:07,433 --> 00:06:09,731
Sorry, I'm late.

53
00:06:14,307 --> 00:06:16,366
Hey, hey...
what are you doing?

54
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:18,969
You've lost a button.

55
00:06:19,011 --> 00:06:21,002
Than! Get those plates
to table two.

56
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:22,708
Yes, ma'am.

57
00:06:35,595 --> 00:06:37,620
Cheers,
my darling.

58
00:06:38,698 --> 00:06:40,859
One two three--

59
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,733
Wobbly custard.

60
00:06:45,204 --> 00:06:46,933
Oh, that's great.

61
00:06:48,641 --> 00:06:51,371
That'll make
Granddad jealous.

62
00:06:51,411 --> 00:06:54,278
I told you this would be
more fun than skiing.

63
00:06:54,313 --> 00:06:56,304
I'm telling you again,

64
00:06:56,349 --> 00:06:59,182
we came here to dive.

65
00:06:59,218 --> 00:07:01,209
Shit.

66
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:04,515
Thank you.

67
00:07:04,557 --> 00:07:06,855
Okay okay.
I'll go diving.

68
00:07:06,893 --> 00:07:09,919
Are you sure they have
a mask that fits you?

69
00:07:10,997 --> 00:07:12,555
Not too early.

70
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:17,131
You shouldn't tease
him like that.

71
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:19,229
It's his holiday too.

72
00:07:19,272 --> 00:07:21,240
Two weeks
in a luxury resort--

73
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:23,401
that boy's got nothing
to complain about.

74
00:07:26,612 --> 00:07:28,876
Oh, no no no.
Not that one.

75
00:07:28,915 --> 00:07:30,780
I think that's us.

76
00:07:30,817 --> 00:07:33,445
- I don't think Daddy likes that music.
- Yeah, let's go.

77
00:07:33,486 --> 00:07:34,919
You won't get up in time.

78
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,751
What? Are you scared
of the water?

79
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:38,689
No, I'm not scared
of the water-- I told you.

80
00:07:38,724 --> 00:07:40,351
- You're just like Dad.
- What?

81
00:07:40,393 --> 00:07:41,951
- Seriously, no--
- Come with me.

82
00:07:41,994 --> 00:07:43,825
No...

83
00:07:43,863 --> 00:07:45,831
What do you reckon?

84
00:07:45,865 --> 00:07:47,332
Ooh.

85
00:07:47,366 --> 00:07:49,391
No rush hour and you
get to see dolphins.

86
00:07:49,435 --> 00:07:53,633
Go on, you go.
I left my snorkel at home anyways.

87
00:07:53,673 --> 00:07:55,072
Yeah?

88
00:07:59,178 --> 00:08:00,577
Just...

89
00:08:00,613 --> 00:08:03,411
don't get
eaten by sharks.

90
00:08:03,449 --> 00:08:05,644
- There aren't any sharks.
- Oh yeah.

91
00:08:05,685 --> 00:08:07,653
Whale sharks.
Native to Thailand.

92
00:08:07,687 --> 00:08:11,521
Also known
as blah chalalam nah.

93
00:08:12,558 --> 00:08:14,253
Hey hey hey.
No no no.

94
00:08:14,293 --> 00:08:17,194
If you watched
a little bit more TV, see--

95
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:20,495
- you'd know.
- Blah belplsey?

96
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:23,934
No no no--
blah chalalam nah.

97
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:25,961
Blah blah blah.

98
00:08:41,554 --> 00:08:43,419
- Hello, friend.
- Hi, hi.

99
00:08:43,456 --> 00:08:46,391
- Not in bed yet?
- No-- just listening to the radio.

100
00:08:46,425 --> 00:08:48,916
- I'm on my way home.
- Good night then.

101
00:09:09,482 --> 00:09:11,643
Grandma...

102
00:09:11,684 --> 00:09:14,619
You stink of fried fish.
Give me your shirt to wash.

103
00:09:20,159 --> 00:09:22,821
- I have something for you.
- Thank you.

104
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:30,925
You're up early!

105
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:33,124
Hurry up-- you have
to go to school.

106
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:46,300
- Thank you, Grandma.
- Have a good day.

107
00:10:46,345 --> 00:10:47,835
Goodbye.

108
00:10:50,616 --> 00:10:53,813
Hurry-- eat up and then
you can go to school.

109
00:11:10,636 --> 00:11:13,799
That's kind of doing it
for me actually.

110
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:21,206
Oh, no ice cream
before lunch.

111
00:11:21,247 --> 00:11:23,181
What are you
on about?

112
00:11:23,215 --> 00:11:24,739
Beach equals ice cream.

113
00:11:24,784 --> 00:11:27,514
That's like toast
without butter.

114
00:11:28,954 --> 00:11:31,445
No, I'm not
talking about Martha.

115
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:35,821
No no. You've got
to be kidding.

116
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:38,193
Oh, who are they?

117
00:11:38,230 --> 00:11:41,666
That's us
swimming in the sea.

118
00:11:41,701 --> 00:11:44,261
Oh yeah?
Where are the sharks?

119
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:47,534
- Shh.
- Come on. Teeth.

120
00:11:47,573 --> 00:11:51,009
- Right, I'm off.
- All right.

121
00:11:53,446 --> 00:11:55,914
In front.

122
00:12:00,319 --> 00:12:01,946
In back.

123
00:12:12,665 --> 00:12:14,633
Hello.

124
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:22,100
- Am I late?
- Don't worry, it's okay.

125
00:12:27,046 --> 00:12:29,514
What are you
looking at?

126
00:12:29,548 --> 00:12:31,038
Come on--
clear the tables.

127
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:33,176
Excuse me.

128
00:12:33,219 --> 00:12:35,153
Could we wait
for my husband please?

129
00:12:35,187 --> 00:12:37,781
Sorry, we really
have to get going.

130
00:12:37,823 --> 00:12:40,519
Great.

131
00:12:40,559 --> 00:12:42,493
- Hi, hello.
- Hi.

132
00:12:42,528 --> 00:12:43,961
- Hello.
- Hello.

133
00:12:43,996 --> 00:12:45,657
Bye, Mommy.

134
00:12:46,899 --> 00:12:48,799
Bye, Mommy.

135
00:13:19,331 --> 00:13:22,027
So we're going
to say hello to Mommy.

136
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:24,194
- Mommy!
- Hello hello.

137
00:13:24,236 --> 00:13:25,726
- Hello, Mommy.
- Bye bye.

138
00:13:25,771 --> 00:13:27,329
Come on, hurry up!

139
00:13:34,947 --> 00:13:37,381
You gonna say hello
to Granddad?

140
00:13:37,416 --> 00:13:39,475
- Hello, Granddad.
- Hello, Granddad.

141
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:43,580
The fish are all funny.

142
00:13:43,622 --> 00:13:46,352
Yeah.

143
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:49,054
- Daft buggers.
- Buggers?

144
00:13:49,094 --> 00:13:52,120
Hey, don't let your mother
hear you say that, okay?

145
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:55,133
Come on, oh, seriously.
Seriously, all right?

146
00:13:57,636 --> 00:13:59,399
Let's go get
your water wings.

147
00:14:02,474 --> 00:14:04,066
John!

148
00:14:05,945 --> 00:14:07,503
Why the hell
didn't Mom wake us?

149
00:14:07,546 --> 00:14:11,038
- She did but we ignored her.
- What?

150
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:13,517
What's happened
to the sea?

151
00:14:13,552 --> 00:14:16,350
It's cool.

152
00:14:27,700 --> 00:14:29,895
What fish
is Nemo?

153
00:14:29,935 --> 00:14:32,836
- Well, he's blue so--
- Orange.

154
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:36,603
- Well, he's blue so--
- Orange!

155
00:14:38,577 --> 00:14:40,738
- Hi.
- Good morning.

156
00:14:40,779 --> 00:14:43,577
- I'd have Nemo with chips.
- No, Daddy.

157
00:14:43,616 --> 00:14:46,881
A little bit
of ketchup. Oh...

158
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:10,405
What's happening, Daddy?

159
00:15:11,944 --> 00:15:14,242
Daddy Daddy?

160
00:15:15,681 --> 00:15:17,740
Come on!

161
00:15:17,783 --> 00:15:20,718
Get in, get in! Come on!

162
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:24,912
Daddy, Daddy.

163
00:15:32,498 --> 00:15:34,830
Don't let go!

164
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:36,698
Don't let--

165
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:46,002
Martha!
Hold on!

166
00:15:46,045 --> 00:15:48,377
Martha, hold on!

167
00:15:50,816 --> 00:15:53,376
Daddy!

168
00:15:53,419 --> 00:15:56,946
- Daddy!
- Martha, hold on!

169
00:15:56,989 --> 00:15:59,583
- Hold the tree!
- Daddy, save me!

170
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:01,422
Hold it, Martha!
Hold the--

171
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:03,690
- Daddy!
- Hold the tree! Grab the tree!

172
00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:05,890
Grab the tree!

173
00:16:05,931 --> 00:16:07,762
Hold on, Martha!

174
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,290
That's it, baby!
Hold on!

175
00:16:09,335 --> 00:16:11,565
Hold on!
Hold on!

176
00:16:11,603 --> 00:16:12,797
Hold on!

177
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:17,166
Hold on!
Hold on, baby!

178
00:16:18,277 --> 00:16:20,677
Hold on!
Hold tight!

179
00:16:20,713 --> 00:16:23,079
- Mommy!
- Hold on, Marth--

180
00:16:37,062 --> 00:16:39,758
Guys, guys.
A bit of hush in the back.

181
00:16:39,798 --> 00:16:41,663
Thank you.

182
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:44,692
So I've asked myself,
how is it

183
00:16:44,737 --> 00:16:47,399
that I've ended up lumbered
with you lot over Christmas?

184
00:16:49,108 --> 00:16:52,100
I mean, what a ragbag collection
of waifs and strays we are.

185
00:16:52,144 --> 00:16:54,874
You know, we're going to be
found out one of these days.

186
00:16:54,913 --> 00:16:57,381
I mean, just look at it.

187
00:16:57,416 --> 00:16:59,543
As many of you know,
my ex-wife used to say,

188
00:16:59,585 --> 00:17:01,746
"You might as well
be married to the job."

189
00:17:01,787 --> 00:17:04,347
All I can say is
it's been a very happy affair.

190
00:17:04,390 --> 00:17:06,858
And it's time for some
thank yous:

191
00:17:06,892 --> 00:17:09,884
To the lovely Sue,
for keeping my diary in shape;

192
00:17:09,928 --> 00:17:13,420
And to all of you who are
committed to working so hard

193
00:17:13,465 --> 00:17:15,433
with the people
of Thailand.

194
00:17:15,467 --> 00:17:17,662
I certainly couldn't do
my job without you.

195
00:17:19,071 --> 00:17:21,403
So to those of us

196
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:24,898
- who haven't skived off on holiday...
- Hi.

197
00:17:24,943 --> 00:17:27,036
...I'd like to raise
my glass of festive fizz

198
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:29,775
and wish you all
a very happy Christmas.

199
00:17:29,815 --> 00:17:31,407
Happy Christmas!

200
00:17:37,322 --> 00:17:40,348
Alec, this is Tom Philips,
who's recently joined us.

201
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:42,292
Hello, Tom.
Nice to meet you.

202
00:17:42,327 --> 00:17:46,286
Lovely children, they're from the
coastal villages. Aren't they fantastic?

203
00:17:46,331 --> 00:17:47,889
Absolutely charming.

204
00:17:52,638 --> 00:17:54,435
I think the...

205
00:17:54,473 --> 00:17:57,499
little one's meant to be
the evil twin.

206
00:17:59,178 --> 00:18:00,907
Will you excuse me?

207
00:18:08,487 --> 00:18:10,648
Reports are sketchy,

208
00:18:10,689 --> 00:18:13,089
but it seems to have hit
Indonesia and Sri Lanka first.

209
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:14,922
- Bev?
- Drafting in everyone she can.

210
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,689
The phones have
gone ballistic.

211
00:18:16,728 --> 00:18:18,787
And here, Patong
and possibly Krabi.

212
00:18:18,831 --> 00:18:22,790
Ah, I've already had calls from CNN,
BBC World, and uh--

213
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:24,996
- Put London straight through.
- Sir.

214
00:18:25,037 --> 00:18:27,631
Robert, Christine, both Peters
are out of the country.

215
00:18:27,673 --> 00:18:29,800
Daniel and his girlfriend
are on holiday.

216
00:18:29,842 --> 00:18:32,436
Well, call him in. We're gonna
need his input on this.

217
00:18:32,478 --> 00:18:35,606
No one's answering.
They were staying near Phuket.

218
00:18:35,647 --> 00:18:37,547
We're gonna need
more phone lines.

219
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:40,313
Get one of Hanuman's boys
to set that up as soon as possible.

220
00:18:40,352 --> 00:18:42,843
The emails coming in
have crashed the system.

221
00:18:46,658 --> 00:18:48,285
London...

222
00:18:48,327 --> 00:18:50,295
line one.

223
00:18:52,564 --> 00:18:54,691
Mark?

224
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,701
What have you got
for me?

225
00:18:56,735 --> 00:18:58,362
Yes, I'm just looking.

226
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:07,175
Christ.

227
00:19:33,772 --> 00:19:35,763
Yeah?

228
00:19:35,807 --> 00:19:38,002
Nick, Nick,
turn on the TV.

229
00:19:38,043 --> 00:19:41,342
Some kind of wave's
hit the south.

230
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:43,371
Chaku Chak Park,
10 minutes, okay?

231
00:19:43,415 --> 00:19:45,280
Suk?

232
00:19:45,317 --> 00:19:46,807
Simone wants us
to cover it.

233
00:19:46,852 --> 00:19:49,252
Simone fired me,
right?

234
00:19:49,288 --> 00:19:50,812
You got
your job back.

235
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:52,619
It's Christmas.
I swung it.

236
00:19:52,658 --> 00:19:54,717
Don't be late,
they're closing the airport.

237
00:19:56,762 --> 00:19:58,195
Where are we going?

238
00:19:58,230 --> 00:20:00,994
Phuket. Look, I'm serious,
don't be late, okay?

239
00:20:19,451 --> 00:20:21,043
Ah.

240
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,723
Help--

241
00:20:31,029 --> 00:20:32,826
Help me!

242
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:37,497
Martha!

243
00:20:40,372 --> 00:20:41,999
Somebody help me!

244
00:21:04,496 --> 00:21:06,020
Martha!

245
00:21:10,068 --> 00:21:12,059
Higher ground.

246
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:13,731
We have to go
higher ground.

247
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:17,208
- Martha!
- Maybe second wave coming.

248
00:21:17,242 --> 00:21:20,040
There more wave.

249
00:21:20,078 --> 00:21:21,909
Martha!

250
00:21:22,981 --> 00:21:25,245
Everything gone.

251
00:21:39,931 --> 00:21:42,729
Run, run!

252
00:21:43,735 --> 00:21:45,430
We must get
to safe place.

253
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:47,233
She was holding
the tree.

254
00:21:47,272 --> 00:21:49,502
Martha!

255
00:21:49,541 --> 00:21:51,771
They have gone
to higher ground.

256
00:21:51,810 --> 00:21:53,869
Please?

257
00:21:53,912 --> 00:21:55,743
- If it come again--
- Martha!

258
00:22:10,696 --> 00:22:12,823
Martha!

259
00:22:20,305 --> 00:22:22,933
Martha!

260
00:22:26,912 --> 00:22:28,812
Martha!

261
00:22:33,018 --> 00:22:35,919
We take Jim's car.
Bev, Sue and the others will follow.

262
00:22:35,954 --> 00:22:37,717
You sure there's
no way we can fly?

263
