He won't be safe here.
His family...

528
00:49:10,480 --> 00:49:12,311
they'll wanna bury him.

529
00:49:15,619 --> 00:49:17,553
I have to find
my family.

530
00:49:19,923 --> 00:49:22,187
Make sure he's okay.

531
00:49:22,225 --> 00:49:24,523
His name's James.

532
00:49:24,561 --> 00:49:27,860
He was staying
at the Khao Lak Oasis.

533
00:49:27,898 --> 00:49:29,866
Don't leave him here.

534
00:49:32,169 --> 00:49:34,899
Oliver! Go!

535
00:50:25,122 --> 00:50:27,022
Run! Run!
The police are here!

536
00:50:30,694 --> 00:50:32,286
It's just milk!

537
00:50:33,363 --> 00:50:35,354
It's not for me.

538
00:50:35,399 --> 00:50:37,833
I'm heading back
to my village.

539
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:39,426
There are people
trapped...

540
00:50:39,469 --> 00:50:41,835
I can't find anyone
to help.

541
00:50:44,674 --> 00:50:47,165
You've been stealing
from the tourists?

542
00:50:47,210 --> 00:50:49,371
No-- they're
my grandmother's...

543
00:51:47,437 --> 00:51:50,838
They took
her body away.

544
00:52:48,665 --> 00:52:51,361
I'm looking
for my wife.

545
00:52:51,401 --> 00:52:53,335
Oh...

546
00:52:53,370 --> 00:52:58,433
I-I-- I saw... a bed,
it was empty.

547
00:53:06,082 --> 00:53:08,516
Where do I go?

548
00:53:08,552 --> 00:53:10,076
Ah...

549
00:54:42,846 --> 00:54:44,609
Hang on a sec.

550
00:54:51,388 --> 00:54:54,687
They're burning
unidentified bodies, Simone.

551
00:54:58,795 --> 00:55:01,457
I saw... a woman,

552
00:55:01,498 --> 00:55:03,489
a child.
I saw two men.

553
00:55:03,533 --> 00:55:05,660
- Westerners?
- Yeah, Thais, too.

554
00:55:05,702 --> 00:55:08,296
There's 50 or 60 bodies
lined up, ready to go.

555
00:55:08,338 --> 00:55:11,102
- Okay, Chai got shots?
- Yeah, we'll send them to you now.

556
00:55:11,141 --> 00:55:12,938
Shots from the beach,
give her those.

557
00:55:12,976 --> 00:55:14,910
Back off, Nick.

558
00:55:14,944 --> 00:55:17,037
They're burning
Westerners, Chai.

559
00:55:18,915 --> 00:55:20,576
- They're dead.
- I got the shot.

560
00:55:20,617 --> 00:55:22,881
- It's my camera.
- Those people have families, Chai.

561
00:55:22,919 --> 00:55:25,888
You felt the heat today.
The monks have to protect the living,

562
00:55:25,922 --> 00:55:27,822
and those bodies will
spread infection.

563
00:55:27,857 --> 00:55:29,620
Yeah well, we like
our bodies in a box.

564
00:55:29,659 --> 00:55:31,490
It's more than just
a souvenir to take home.

565
00:55:31,528 --> 00:55:34,088
Families like
to gather together, say goodbye...

566
00:55:35,598 --> 00:55:37,395
...maybe even say
the odd prayer.

567
00:55:37,434 --> 00:55:39,129
It's what we
call a funeral.

568
00:55:39,169 --> 00:55:41,763
Don't patronize me.
We syndicate that shot--

569
00:55:41,805 --> 00:55:44,569
- It's a good shot.
- It says we don't care.

570
00:55:44,607 --> 00:55:47,235
You don't get it because you don't
live your life like we do.

571
00:55:47,277 --> 00:55:50,644
To us, the body is just a vessel,
what carries us through this life.

572
00:55:50,680 --> 00:55:53,410
And when it dies, the spirit's
released into the next.

573
00:55:54,818 --> 00:55:57,309
I'm sorry, Chai.

574
00:56:02,158 --> 00:56:04,023
You saw the monks
helping people.

575
00:56:04,060 --> 00:56:07,723
You saw them praying. But who cares
about that as long as you get the shot?

576
00:56:07,764 --> 00:56:09,994
- It'll stop it.
- People will look at that shot,

577
00:56:10,033 --> 00:56:12,501
and even though it's fine for you
to come here for holidays

578
00:56:12,535 --> 00:56:14,833
and drop your tabs on the beach
and love the food, yeah?

579
00:56:14,871 --> 00:56:17,169
- That shot--
- It'll make governments listen.

580
00:56:17,207 --> 00:56:19,334
It slams us right back
into the Third World,

581
00:56:19,376 --> 00:56:22,368
and that's fine for you.
You're not Thai.

582
00:56:27,117 --> 00:56:29,711
I need a photo
of my wife and daughter.

583
00:56:31,221 --> 00:56:32,654
I'm sorry?

584
00:56:32,689 --> 00:56:34,987
I need to use
a phone.

585
00:56:35,024 --> 00:56:36,457
Oh.

586
00:56:36,493 --> 00:56:38,461
Here you go.

587
00:56:40,463 --> 00:56:43,296
I sent one
to my dad yesterday.

588
00:56:48,538 --> 00:56:50,733
Want me to do that
for you?

589
00:56:52,442 --> 00:56:54,910
- It's U.K.?
- Yeah.

590
00:56:54,944 --> 00:56:57,037
It's London.
0-2-0-7--

591
00:57:06,222 --> 00:57:08,486
Mm-hmm.

592
00:57:17,467 --> 00:57:19,435
Now it's ringing.

593
00:57:24,007 --> 00:57:26,134
Hi, Dad.

594
00:57:37,320 --> 00:57:39,220
Right.

595
00:57:39,255 --> 00:57:42,622
BBC, CNN, Asian News,
they're all here.

596
00:57:42,659 --> 00:57:45,355
Grab your powder puffs,
ladies.

597
00:57:50,900 --> 00:57:54,392
Right, we need to get
our office set up.

598
00:57:56,739 --> 00:57:58,434
Tony?

599
00:58:01,077 --> 00:58:03,045
I'll set up a press briefing,
A.S.A.P.

600
00:58:03,079 --> 00:58:06,048
No, I'd like to hit the hotel first.
Maybe a quick debrief.

601
00:58:06,082 --> 00:58:08,573
Make sense of how
we're gonna coordinate things.

602
00:58:08,618 --> 00:58:10,347
You're kidding,
right?

603
00:58:10,386 --> 00:58:13,446
Tony, you're not going to be seeing
a hotel room for quite awhile.

604
00:58:14,991 --> 00:58:16,959
They have it
upstairs.

605
00:58:29,472 --> 00:58:30,837
Okay?

606
00:58:39,682 --> 00:58:41,673
Well, the Aussies look
pretty settled.

607
00:58:41,718 --> 00:58:43,481
Where do we sit?

608
00:58:43,520 --> 00:58:47,149
I think people have got a grip
on what's actually happened here.

609
00:58:47,190 --> 00:58:49,283
Excuse me,
excuse me.

610
00:58:49,325 --> 00:58:52,158
Joe, clear all that stuff,
will you?

611
00:58:53,563 --> 00:58:55,360
Are you
from the British consul?

612
00:58:55,398 --> 00:58:57,059
Look, we're gonna need
some sort of flag--

613
00:58:57,100 --> 00:58:58,499
- Helen!
- Maybe some notepaper.

614
00:58:58,535 --> 00:59:00,901
And coffee--
I'm gonna need coffee.

615
00:59:00,937 --> 00:59:02,666
Where the fuck
have you been?

616
00:59:02,705 --> 00:59:04,605
I lost my son
and my daughters.

617
00:59:04,641 --> 00:59:07,508
All right, all right, one at a time,
please. Just one at a time.

618
00:59:10,647 --> 00:59:12,342
Joe, Joe, Joe!

619
00:59:12,382 --> 00:59:14,145
What's your name, sir?

620
00:59:15,818 --> 00:59:18,582
We're-- we're gonna need
some more volunteers.

621
00:59:18,621 --> 00:59:20,111
All right, all right,
please--

622
00:59:31,301 --> 00:59:32,825
Thanks.

623
00:59:37,373 --> 00:59:40,774
We were just standing
on the beach.

624
00:59:40,810 --> 00:59:43,643
We went back 'cause--

625
00:59:43,680 --> 00:59:46,080
my wife...

626
00:59:46,115 --> 00:59:48,413
she always wants her
to wear her water wings.

627
00:59:51,287 --> 00:59:53,687
She was holding on
to a tree.

628
00:59:57,460 --> 01:00:00,293
She's only six,
but she's--

629
01:00:00,330 --> 01:00:03,595
she's got a real
strong grip.

630
01:00:10,440 --> 01:00:12,704
What do you think?

631
01:00:13,943 --> 01:00:16,104
She was holding on
to a tree.

632
01:00:20,817 --> 01:00:23,752
I'd say your kid's
still alive.

633
01:00:36,499 --> 01:00:39,332
"I'd say your kid's
still alive"?

634
01:01:01,691 --> 01:01:03,886
...arriving here
in the disaster zone.

635
01:01:03,926 --> 01:01:06,190
Britain's representative,
Tony Whittaker,

636
01:01:06,229 --> 01:01:09,665
arrived early this morning,
and is here with me now.

637
01:01:09,699 --> 01:01:12,463
Do you as yet
have any figure

638
01:01:12,502 --> 01:01:14,970
as to how high the death toll
could climb?

639
01:01:15,004 --> 01:01:17,165
It's really too early
to say, but what is clear

640
01:01:17,206 --> 01:01:19,367
is that this is
a catastrophe for Thailand,

641
01:01:19,409 --> 01:01:21,536
and indeed the whole
of the Andaman Coast.

642
01:01:21,577 --> 01:01:24,478
Right now, we're trying to assess
which areas have been worst hit.

643
01:01:24,514 --> 01:01:26,880
- Khao Lak looks very bad.
- Are you aware that bodies

644
01:01:26,916 --> 01:01:29,384
are being burned in the temple
just outside of there?

645
01:01:29,419 --> 01:01:32,047
- There are a number of rumors--
- No, I've seen the bodies.

646
01:01:32,088 --> 01:01:35,148
Westerners and Thais being
cremated without identification.

647
01:01:35,191 --> 01:01:38,592
I-- I'm following it up.
But, it's my understanding

648
01:01:38,628 --> 01:01:41,222
that no Western bodies
are being cremated.

649
01:01:41,264 --> 01:01:43,061
Their focus is very much

650
01:01:43,099 --> 01:01:46,068
on the identification,
preservation and return

651
01:01:46,102 --> 01:01:48,468
- of those bodies to loved ones.
- The Thai government--

652
01:01:48,504 --> 01:01:51,098
That's really all we have time for.
There's a lot to do.

653
01:01:51,140 --> 01:01:52,869
Get London
on the phone.

654
01:01:54,877 --> 01:01:57,368
Excuse me?
Excuse me, I'm--

655
01:01:57,413 --> 01:01:59,813
we're-- I'm trying to find
my husband and my son,

656
01:01:59,849 --> 01:02:02,374
but nobody-- nobody seems
to know where we should be.

657
01:02:02,418 --> 01:02:04,716
Have you tried talking
to your tour operator?

658
01:02:04,754 --> 01:02:07,814
I don't have a tour operator.
We organized this holiday ourselves.

659
01:02:07,857 --> 01:02:10,257
We're hoping to arrange
some evacuation flights,

660
01:02:10,293 --> 01:02:12,227
but at the present
it's impractical.

661
01:02:12,261 --> 01:02:13,455
Is that Mark?

662
01:02:13,496 --> 01:02:15,828
- Uh--
- Mark?

663
01:02:15,865 --> 01:02:17,560
Nice one, Mom.

664
01:02:21,070 --> 01:02:23,163
If you can
head back to Krabi,

665
01:02:23,206 --> 01:02:25,766
I'll head up as far North
as I can.

666
01:02:25,808 --> 01:02:28,641
Let's cover five villages
each today.

667
01:02:28,678 --> 01:02:31,647
That's fifteen between us.

668
01:02:31,681 --> 01:02:33,649
Hi, Kathy speaking.

669
01:02:33,683 --> 01:02:35,150
Mm-hmm?

670
01:02:35,184 --> 01:02:37,209
I'm looking for my father
and my brother.

671
01:02:37,253 --> 01:02:38,515
Here, take this.

672
01:02:38,554 --> 01:02:40,351
I don't want
a bar of soap.

673
01:02:40,389 --> 01:02:41,913
Adam, look,
calm down.

674
01:02:41,958 --> 01:02:43,687
They could be dead.

675
01:02:43,726 --> 01:02:45,990
Hey hey.

676
01:02:46,028 --> 01:02:47,518
I don't need
a bar of soap.

677
01:02:47,563 --> 01:02:49,258
No, but you do
need some sleep.

678
01:02:49,298 --> 01:02:51,528
Across the street and to the left,
they've opened up

679
01:02:51,567 --> 01:02:53,797
the college gym.
You can get a bed and a hot shower.

680
01:02:53,836 --> 01:02:55,667
You should take
all you can right now.

681
01:02:55,705 --> 01:02:57,570
You don't know how long
it's gonna last.

682
01:02:57,607 --> 01:03:00,098
Thank you,
thanks.

683
01:03:00,143 --> 01:03:01,940
It's James...

684
01:03:03,079 --> 01:03:04,239
sorry.

685
01:03:04,280 --> 01:03:05,611
It's okay.

686
01:03:05,648 --> 01:03:06,910
James Robert Peabody.

687
01:03:06,949 --> 01:03:10,441
11th of the 11th, 1960;

688
01:03:10,486 --> 01:03:13,353
and John David Peabody,
10th of the 9th, '88.

689
01:03:13,389 --> 01:03:15,254
Yes, they're
on the list.

690
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:17,054
Okay.

691
01:03:18,628 --> 01:03:20,255
Thank you.

692
01:03:23,733 --> 01:03:26,293
Next, please.

693
01:03:26,335 --> 01:03:28,826
We're moving.
Joe's found us a proper office

694
01:03:28,871 --> 01:03:30,862
around the corner
with air conditioning.

695
01:03:30,907 --> 01:03:32,534
You got room
for another one?

696
01:03:32,575 --> 01:03:34,236
It's really just
for U.K. use.

697
01:03:36,078 --> 01:03:38,774
I've got 600 children
missing, Tony.

698
01:03:38,815 --> 01:03:41,340
So far I know 12 of them
are still alive.

699
01:03:43,753 --> 01:03:45,550
It's a bit
rough and ready.

700
01:03:45,588 --> 01:03:47,783
"Chaos is a friend
of mine."

701
01:03:47,824 --> 01:03:49,519
It's Bob Dylan.

702
01:03:53,296 --> 01:03:54,888
So what are you saying?

703
01:03:54,931 --> 01:03:56,922
No one's
picking up the story.

704
01:03:56,966 --> 01:03:58,831
You're kidding me?

705
01:03:58,868 --> 01:04:00,961
There are no Westerners
on the photo.

706
01:04:01,003 --> 01:04:03,198
There was a woman,
she had light brown hair...

707
01:04:03,239 --> 01:04:04,763
she's probably
European.

708
01:04:04,807 --> 01:04:07,742
Yeah, she looks black,
bloody and dead.

709
01:04:07,777 --> 01:04:11,076
Look, your word isn't enough
for anyone to print it. It's too risky.

710
01:04:11,113 --> 01:04:13,411
They're burning Thais.
Adds up to the same thing.

711
01:04:13,449 --> 01:04:15,974
They're incinerating people
without identification.

712
01:04:16,018 --> 01:04:18,816
It's been stopped.
Someone yelled at the Thais.

713
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:20,948
Reuters just
tipped me off.

714
01:04:20,990 --> 01:04:23,356
The story's done.
Move on.

715
01:04:23,392 --> 01:04:25,292
People need evidence.

716
01:04:25,328 --> 01:04:27,159
I gave you evidence.

717
01:04:27,196 --> 01:04:29,596
Next Christmas
I'm going to Malibu.

718
01:05:03,499 --> 01:05:05,660
This is
a 20-minute walk.

719
01:05:05,701 --> 01:05:07,760
15 if you're brisk.

720
01:05:07,803 --> 01:05:11,534
You're not worried that people
won't be able to find you?

721
01:05:13,276 --> 01:05:15,506
Phone sockets,
internet points.

722
01:05:15,544 --> 01:05:19,002
We've got more volunteers arriving
tomorrow. They'll need every line.

723
01:05:19,048 --> 01:05:22,984
We can field calls, relatives
can make "missing" posters.

724
01:05:23,019 --> 01:05:25,317
You'll need a contact point
in every hospital.

725
01:05:25,354 --> 01:05:27,584
Yeah, I think if we
make this our base...

726
01:05:27,623 --> 01:05:30,353
Khao Lak is over
an hour away.

727
01:05:30,393 --> 01:05:32,827
It's a long way to walk
if you've lost your family

728
01:05:32,862 --> 01:05:35,160
and all your money
and don't speak Thai.

729
01:05:36,565 --> 01:05:39,398
Just an observation.

730
01:05:41,103 --> 01:05:44,402
Good good.
If you want to get some tea going?

731
01:05:44,440 --> 01:05:47,671
Call's just come through.
Attaché's arriving at 4:00.

732
01:05:50,680 --> 01:05:52,773
Hello?

733
01:05:52,815 --> 01:05:54,476
Yeah.

734
01:06:06,128 --> 01:06:08,187
I'm lost.

735
01:06:08,230 --> 01:06:10,562
Come.
Come sit down.

736
01:06:12,101 --> 01:06:14,228
I need to get back
to my village!

737
01:06:14,270 --> 01:06:18,206
There are people
trapped...

738
01:06:18,240 --> 01:06:21,107
Please...
Please let me out.

739
01:06:46,535 --> 01:06:48,400
Is this it?

740
01:06:48,437 --> 01:06:51,304
Came through
from your dad.

741
01:06:57,413 --> 01:06:58,675
Shall I?

742
01:07:15,331 --> 01:07:17,196
They're some
of my kids.

743
01:07:17,233 --> 01:07:19,428
I work with
an education program,

744
01:07:19,468 --> 01:07:21,561
mainly in
the fishing villages.

745
01:07:21,604 --> 01:07:24,129
Those are the ones
we've found so far.

746
01:07:24,173 --> 01:07:26,903
- That's good.
- It's a start.

747
01:07:35,384 --> 01:07:38,251
Maybe you should try
and get some sleep?

748
01:08:20,830 --> 01:08:22,161
Ian!

749
01:08:23,566 --> 01:08:25,864
Oh my God!

750
01:08:28,571 --> 01:08:30,038
Susan!

751
01:08:33,375 --> 01:08:35,240
Susan, I thought
you were dead.

752
01:08:35,277 --> 01:08:38,007
I thought-- I thought you--
I thought you were dead.

753
01:08:38,047 --> 01:08:39,981
The boat came back,
everything was gone.

754
01:08:40,015 --> 01:08:42,643
Everything--
the chalet, the hotel,

755
01:08:42,685 --> 01:08:44,915
it was all gone.
Where's Martha?

756
01:08:44,954 --> 01:08:46,717
Where's Martha?
She was with you.

757
01:08:46,755 --> 01:08:50,316
We were-- we were coming back
to the hotel. She got hold of a tree,

758
01:08:50,359 --> 01:08:52,054
I don't know where she is.

759
01:08:52,094 --> 01:08:56,588
No no, she's alive.
Susan, Martha's-- Martha's alive.

760
01:08:56,632 --> 01:08:59,430
This guy, he said he
saw her, just outside--

761
01:08:59,468 --> 01:09:01,629
- What guy saw her?
- This guy.

762
01:09:01,670 --> 01:09:03,968
She wasn't letting go.

763
01:09:04,006 --> 01:09:07,806
Nothing was gonna
make her let go, see?

764
01:09:09,078 --> 01:09:10,978
She's alive.
We're gonna find her.

765
01:09:11,013 --> 01:09:13,846
Baby...

766
01:09:13,883 --> 01:09:16,943
- never leave me again.
- No.

767
01:09:16,986 --> 01:09:19,454
You never leave me.

768
01:09:19,488 --> 01:09:20,750
Oh no.

769
01:09:41,844 --> 01:09:44,005
We're gonna
find her, baby.

770
01:09:46,749 --> 01:09:48,842
We're gonna find her.

771
01:10:09,705 --> 01:10:11,332
- Hi, Ralph.
- Hey, Nick.

772
01:10:11,373 --> 01:10:13,739
Ron.

773
01:10:13,776 --> 01:10:15,437
Wanker.

774
01:10:17,112 --> 01:10:18,340
Here.

775
01:10:18,380 --> 01:10:20,109
Thanks.

776
01:10:27,089 --> 01:10:29,421
How come is all the
palm trees still standing

777
01:10:29,458 --> 01:10:30,982
and the buildings
are gone?

778
01:10:31,026 --> 01:10:33,392
There you are.
Do we have a rebuilt timeline?

779
01:10:33,429 --> 01:10:34,919
Too early to tell.

780
01:10:34,964 --> 01:10:37,558
- You've got figures?
- 700 missing.

781
01:10:37,600 --> 01:10:41,593
At Khao Lak Oasis,
the occupancy was around 300.

782
01:10:41,637 --> 01:10:43,901
Jesus.

783
01:10:45,808 --> 01:10:47,901
I need to get
more information.

784
01:10:50,246 --> 01:10:52,043
Right.

785
01:10:59,488 --> 01:11:01,115
Let's go.

786
01:11:02,291 --> 01:11:04,521
- Let's go.
- I'm not done.

787
01:11:39,228 --> 01:11:41,788
You okay?

788
01:11:49,905 --> 01:11:51,839
Here.

789
01:11:51,874 --> 01:11:54,240
Put some of this
around your nose.

790
01:11:54,276 --> 01:11:56,301
It helps
with the smell.

791
01:11:56,345 --> 01:11:57,869
Thanks.

792
01:12:07,056 --> 01:12:09,286
Ellen. Ellen Webb.

793
01:12:09,325 --> 01:12:13,193
I work for S.Q.A. Hotels,
managing their properties down here.

794
01:12:13,228 --> 01:12:16,720
Nick Fraser,
East Asia Press.

795
01:12:19,601 --> 01:12:22,195
I was just here
a couple of weeks ago.

796
01:12:24,239 --> 01:12:27,436
We've got hotels
all over the world, but this place--

797
01:12:27,476 --> 01:12:28,909
Mm.

798
01:12:28,944 --> 01:12:30,844
this was really special.

799
01:12:32,948 --> 01:12:36,440
People come here to forget the shit
in their lives and then this happens.

800
01:12:36,485 --> 01:12:38,715
700 missing guests,

801
01:12:38,754 --> 01:12:42,554
that's a lot of unpaid
room service, isn't it?

802
01:12:42,591 --> 01:12:45,321
That's not
what I meant.

803
01:12:45,361 --> 01:12:48,797
Will you be offering some kind
of compensation package?

804
01:12:51,700 --> 01:12:53,793
I just manage
the properties.

805
01:13:07,049 --> 01:13:09,779
I just gotta--
I've just gotta see someone.

806
01:13:20,796 --> 01:13:24,095
- Hi.
- Hi.

807
01:13:24,133 --> 01:13:27,330
We were staying
at the same hotel.

808
01:13:27,369 --> 01:13:29,599
Yeah.

809
01:13:39,081 --> 01:13:42,244
Everyone is calling this
a natural disaster.

810
01:13:44,520 --> 01:13:47,216
I don't know what's natural
about something

811
01:13:47,256 --> 01:13:49,281
that flips
the world on its head.

812
01:13:52,928 --> 01:13:56,022
People monitor earthquakes,
don't they?

813
01:14:01,437 --> 01:14:03,962
It doesn't make sense.

814
01:14:15,417 --> 01:14:17,942
Your husband's dead.

815
01:14:19,755 --> 01:14:23,247
He, um, he died en route
to the hospital.

816
01:14:24,293 --> 01:14:26,227
Yesterday.

817
01:14:26,261 --> 01:14:29,253
About...

818
01:14:29,298 --> 01:14:31,459
it was late.

819
01:14:31,500 --> 01:14:34,162
I don't know
where his body is.

820
01:14:36,305 --> 01:14:38,068
I had to leave him

821
01:14:38,106 --> 01:14:39,937
just north of Khao Lak.

822
01:14:41,844 --> 01:14:43,436
I'm sorry.

823
01:14:44,847 --> 01:14:46,314
Mom!

824
01:14:46,348 --> 01:14:48,714
There's a John Peabody
at Takua Pa Clinic.

825
01:14:49,952 --> 01:14:52,147
He's injured, but--

826
01:14:52,187 --> 01:14:53,586
Please...

827
01:14:53,622 --> 01:14:55,613
don't tell my son yet.

828
01:14:55,657 --> 01:14:57,522
Please.

829
01:14:57,559 --> 01:15:01,656
We're going that way.

830
01:15:33,529 --> 01:15:37,021
Someone said they're
burning the bodies.

831
01:15:38,600 --> 01:15:40,431
What do you mean?

832
01:15:40,469 --> 01:15:43,563
The monks.
They're trying to clear space.

833
01:15:43,605 --> 01:15:47,006
- There's too many dead--
- Adam. Stop it.

834
01:15:47,042 --> 01:15:50,478
- Dad's not here.
- We need to take care of John now.

835
01:15:50,512 --> 01:15:52,343
Dad was half cut
when we left him.

836
01:15:52,381 --> 01:15:54,474
It probably hit him
when he was still in bed--

837
01:16:02,324 --> 01:16:04,758
- I'm sorry, Mom.
- I'm sorry.

838
01:16:04,793 --> 01:16:07,523
- Dad'll be okay.
- I have to go.

839
01:16:10,933 --> 01:16:13,333
Take it, take it.

840
01:16:13,368 --> 01:16:16,269
Susan, Susan!

841
01:16:17,906 --> 01:16:19,271
Susan!

842
01:16:22,177 --> 01:16:24,543
We need to deal
with John now.

843
01:16:26,915 --> 01:16:28,610
And Daddy...

844
01:16:33,221 --> 01:16:36,213
he'd want me
to look after John.

845
01:16:40,696 --> 01:16:44,393
Susan! Don't go
in there, babe.

846
01:16:46,868 --> 01:16:50,031
What if she's dead, Ian?
What if they've burned her body?

847
01:16:50,072 --> 01:16:52,905
Well, you'd just
left the beach.

848
01:16:52,941 --> 01:16:55,239
You'd already--
you'd already been swimming.

849
01:16:55,277 --> 01:16:56,972
She was wearing
her water wings.

850
01:16:57,012 --> 01:16:59,879
No, we were going back
to the room. I'd left them in the room.

851
01:16:59,915 --> 01:17:01,576
She wasn't wearing them?

852
01:17:01,617 --> 01:17:04,017
I had her
in my arms.

853
01:17:04,052 --> 01:17:05,883
You let go?

854
01:17:09,658 --> 01:17:12,559
She got hold
of a tree.

855
01:17:12,594 --> 01:17:15,324
If we go back...

856
01:17:17,165 --> 01:17:19,531
You didn't feel it,
Suze.

857
01:17:19,568 --> 01:17:21,593
You couldn't.

858
01:17:23,071 --> 01:17:26,131
If we go back
to the tree...

859
01:17:28,410 --> 01:17:30,708
Come on, baby.

860
01:17:30,746 --> 01:17:33,738
We'll find her,
we'll find her, baby.

861
01:17:37,886 --> 01:17:40,252
Come on, come on.

862
01:17:40,288 --> 01:17:42,153
Come on.

863
01:19:20,655 --> 01:19:22,384
Careful.

864
01:20:03,431 --> 01:20:05,763
Excuse me?

865
01:20:05,801 --> 01:20:08,599
Excuse me, I'm sorry,
I'm looking for my son?

866
01:20:08,637 --> 01:20:11,037
Do you speak English?

867
01:20:11,072 --> 01:20:12,835
Mom.

868
01:20:22,851 --> 01:20:26,082
Tony. There's a boy
at a clinic in Takua Pa.

869
01:20:26,121 --> 01:20:29,056
John Peabody, 16 years old,
he's badly injured.

870
01:20:29,090 --> 01:20:32,253
His mother called while you were out
and she needs a flight evacuation.

871
01:20:32,294 --> 01:20:34,558
There are spaces on the commercial
charters if need be.

872
01:20:34,596 --> 01:20:36,063
Do people know that?

873
01:20:37,299 --> 01:20:39,199
The second team
arrive tomorrow.

874
01:20:39,234 --> 01:20:41,464
I'll post someone out there
as soon as it's feasible.

875
01:20:41,503 --> 01:20:43,027
His mother's pretty
distressed.

876
01:20:43,071 --> 01:20:45,801
We have limited resources, Kathy.
I have to coordinate the volunteers

877
01:20:45,841 --> 01:20:47,536
- as best as I can.
- Yeah, I know but--

878
01:20:47,576 --> 01:20:49,874
Why don't you just let me
get on with my job

879
01:20:49,911 --> 01:20:52,072
- and you get back to yours?
- Kathy?

880
01:20:55,183 --> 01:20:57,413
They've arrested some
of the villagers

881
01:20:57,452 --> 01:21:00,615
for looting food
and water.

882
01:21:08,296 --> 01:21:11,629
I can get an official
down here.

883
01:21:11,666 --> 01:21:13,293
One phone call.

884
01:21:18,139 --> 01:21:20,573
Have they been given
food and water?

885
01:21:26,815 --> 01:21:29,249
Does anyone need a lift
to their village?

886
01:21:39,861 --> 01:21:41,692
I need to get
to Kaw Tai village...

887
01:21:44,199 --> 01:21:48,033
They took
Grandmother's bracelets...

888
01:21:54,109 --> 01:21:56,202
No, Mr. Whittaker's
not here at the moment.

889
01:21:56,244 --> 01:21:57,802
What time
will he be back?

890
01:21:57,846 --> 01:22:00,246
He's on an inspection tour,
but there is an open meeting

891
01:22:00,282 --> 01:22:02,716
tonight at the town hall
if you want to ask any questions.

892
01:22:02,751 --> 01:22:05,811
Does anybody-- does anybody in the U.K.
even know what's happening here?

893
01:22:05,854 --> 01:22:08,084
People can't get home.
We don't have any money.

894
01:22:08,123 --> 01:22:09,715
We-- we can't find
our daughter.

895
01:22:09,758 --> 01:22:12,192
You understand?
This is madness.

896
01:22:12,227 --> 01:22:14,388
Ian, Ian!

897
01:22:18,199 --> 01:22:20,565
She's at Takua Pa Clinic.

898
01:22:20,602 --> 01:22:23,264
Oh my God.

899
01:22:23,305 --> 01:22:25,273
It's her?

900
01:22:26,274 --> 01:22:27,832
It's her.

901
01:22:27,876 --> 01:22:29,173
It is her.

902
01:22:29,210 --> 01:22:31,735
Come on.

903
01:22:35,016 --> 01:22:37,712
Hey hey, Takua Pa?
Takua Pa.

904
01:22:37,752 --> 01:22:39,310
Takua Pa.

905
01:22:49,564 --> 01:22:51,930
I think he's just
dehydrated,

906
01:22:51,967 --> 01:22:54,162
but he has a cut
on his side.

907
01:23:14,656 --> 01:23:17,216
I'm going around
in circles.

908
01:23:19,761 --> 01:23:22,059
Been calling
the help line.

909
01:23:24,466 --> 01:23:26,627
They just say,
"Go to your embassy."

910
01:23:26,668 --> 01:23:28,135
I'll see what
I can do but--

911
01:23:28,169 --> 01:23:29,830
When Dad gets here--

912
01:23:29,871 --> 01:23:32,339
Your dad's not
getting here, is he?

913
01:23:33,975 --> 01:23:35,738
Who says?

914
01:23:37,278 --> 01:23:39,178
Who says?

915
01:23:51,393 --> 01:23:53,384
Adam...

916
01:24:00,969 --> 01:24:04,666
Dad's--
Dad's dead, darling.

917
01:24:09,978 --> 01:24:11,878
Okay.

918
01:24:14,249 --> 01:24:16,809
Call them again.

919
01:24:18,053 --> 01:24:20,487
What'll they do?

920
01:24:20,522 --> 01:24:24,458
Give us another wash bag
and a mat in the gym?

921
01:24:25,760 --> 01:24:29,821
I want someone here now.
Someone with authority.

922
01:24:29,864 --> 01:24:32,856
Someone who can
get my son home.

923
01:24:32,901 --> 01:24:35,426
These-- these two boys
are all I've got

924
01:24:35,470 --> 01:24:38,633
and I will not lose
another member of my family.

925
01:24:38,673 --> 01:24:41,665
Phuket town hall.
Tonight there's a meeting

926
01:24:41,709 --> 01:24:43,472
for British survivors.

927
01:24:43,511 --> 01:24:45,274
You're his mother.

928
01:24:45,313 --> 01:24:49,477
There's no one better to convince them
if you want John on a flight.

929
01:25:01,763 --> 01:25:05,096
You stay here with your brother.
Don't move.

930
01:25:05,133 --> 01:25:07,693
All right?

931
01:25:30,558 --> 01:25:32,287
Martha, Martha Carter?

932
01:25:32,327 --> 01:25:34,989
Martha Carter--
she's down as, um, 573

933
01:25:35,029 --> 01:25:38,021
- at your website.
- Over there.

934
01:25:48,409 --> 01:25:50,468
Martha baby?

935
01:25:55,183 --> 01:25:57,174
It's, uh, we're looking
at the wrong girl.

936
01:25:57,218 --> 01:25:59,379
It's the wrong--

937
01:26:09,597 --> 01:26:11,326
It's not her.

938
01:26:22,677 --> 01:26:24,406
It looked like her.

939
01:26:26,481 --> 01:26:29,917
- Photo all scratched up...
- Yeah.

940
01:26:29,951 --> 01:26:32,442
She looked like her.

941
01:26:40,495 --> 01:26:42,463
We could take her.

942
01:26:44,265 --> 01:26:45,892
She's got no parents.

943
01:26:45,934 --> 01:26:48,459
Maybe she's lost her parents,
we could take her.

944
01:26:51,806 --> 01:26:54,400
Susie, baby.

945
01:26:56,311 --> 01:26:58,643
We can't take her, no.

946
01:27:00,014 --> 01:27:03,848
I should never have
left Martha.

947
01:27:03,885 --> 01:27:07,184
I should never have
left her with you.

948
01:27:17,165 --> 01:27:20,259
That's a very pretty dress
that dolly has on.

949
01:27:22,937 --> 01:27:25,633
You have a duck here.

950
01:27:28,610 --> 01:27:30,703
That the duck
to kiss the dolly?

951
01:27:57,572 --> 01:27:59,938
You might want to change
to a Thai network, love.

952
01:27:59,974 --> 01:28:01,168
Sorry?

953
01:28:01,209 --> 01:28:03,769
I said you might want
to change to a Thai network.

954
01:28:03,811 --> 01:28:05,779
For some reason,
their masts were barely hit.

955
01:28:05,813 --> 01:28:08,111
Or you could use
the public phone.

956
01:28:08,149 --> 01:28:10,379
But my friend might
be some time.

957
01:28:10,418 --> 01:28:12,318
You've got a friend.

958
01:28:12,353 --> 01:28:14,378
Yes, I have.

959
01:28:14,422 --> 01:28:16,447
Technology's never
been my thing.

960
01:28:16,491 --> 01:28:18,721
Anything technical,
I always defer to him.

961
01:28:20,061 --> 01:28:22,188
First rule in life.

962
01:28:22,230 --> 01:28:24,960
Always trust the geeks.

963
01:28:24,999 --> 01:28:27,559
Thanks for the tip.

964
01:28:27,602 --> 01:28:29,695
You are most welcome.

965
01:28:36,311 --> 01:28:37,903
You know who he is?

966
01:28:40,982 --> 01:28:42,108
Should I?

967
01:28:42,150 --> 01:28:44,584
Maybe.

968
01:28:53,027 --> 01:28:54,494
Hello, Dr. Meeko.

969
01:28:54,529 --> 01:28:56,156
Boonma.

970
01:28:56,197 --> 01:28:58,825
Look at you,
all smartened up.

971
01:28:58,866 --> 01:29:00,834
Have a seat.

972
01:29:06,474 --> 01:29:09,375
You've been waiting
for this moment a long time.

973
01:29:13,848 --> 01:29:15,008
How can I help you?

974
01:29:17,618 --> 01:29:19,643
On behalf
of the Thai government...

975
01:29:21,489 --> 01:29:25,789
I've a proposition to make,
Dr. Meeko.

976
01:29:49,183 --> 01:29:52,050
Than?
Be back in a sec.

977
01:29:53,154 --> 01:29:54,519
Hey hey.

978
01:29:56,424 --> 01:29:58,324
I have to get back
to my village.

979
01:30:00,194 --> 01:30:01,889
There are people
still alive.

980
01:30:01,929 --> 01:30:03,362
I have to do something.

981
01:30:04,866 --> 01:30:06,993
The villagers have all
run to the hills.

982
01:30:07,034 --> 01:30:09,059
Okay. Okay.

983
01:30:09,103 --> 01:30:11,128
Let's get you cleaned up.

984
01:30:11,172 --> 01:30:12,935
I'll drive you down there.

985
01:30:12,974 --> 01:30:14,771
It'll be okay.

986
01:30:26,487 --> 01:30:28,614
Holy shit.

987
01:32:08,689 --> 01:32:11,590
Tony, the meeting's starting.
We've got to go.

988
01:32:11,626 --> 01:32:13,719
Just coming.

989
01:32:21,035 --> 01:32:24,436
I've been here since last night.
And what have you done? Nothing.

990
01:32:24,472 --> 01:32:28,101
Please, I know you all have questions,
but in a natural disaster of this sort--

991
01:32:28,142 --> 01:32:30,872
No. No.

992
01:32:30,912 --> 01:32:33,107
No.

993
01:32:34,615 --> 01:32:37,948
No, I last saw my daughter
36 hours ago.

994
01:32:39,554 --> 01:32:43,388
She was screaming
for help.

995
01:32:43,424 --> 01:32:45,722
She was alone.

996
01:32:45,760 --> 01:32:48,627
And she was afraid.

997
01:32:48,663 --> 01:32:51,791
There is nothing natural
about any of this.

998
01:32:55,102 --> 01:32:57,400
- I appreciate--
- I want my daughter back.

999
01:32:58,773 --> 01:33:02,675
I want her here,
and I want her now.

1000
01:33:04,178 --> 01:33:06,703
You have to tell me
how to do this.

1001
01:33:08,215 --> 01:33:11,810
Because I'm not leaving
until you do.

1002
01:33:11,852 --> 01:33:14,787
Until all of us...

1003
01:33:16,157 --> 01:33:18,455
get our kids back.

1004
01:33:21,329 --> 01:33:24,230
Believe me, I am going
to do everything I can to help you--

1005
01:33:24,265 --> 01:33:26,597
My wife is dead.
I want her body back.

1006
01:33:26,634 --> 01:33:30,229
My-- my son is lying
in Takua Pa Clinic.

1007
01:33:30,271 --> 01:33:33,638
He will die if he
isn't evacuated tonight.

1008
01:33:33,674 --> 01:33:37,201
Can you guarantee we're
gonna get our bodies back?

1009
01:33:37,244 --> 01:33:41,078
As far we know, there are
up to 10,000 British nationals

1010
01:33:41,115 --> 01:33:43,174
in Thailand at this time.
You can appreciate

1011
01:33:43,217 --> 01:33:45,913
they're trying to coordinate
with the Thai government

1012
01:33:45,953 --> 01:33:49,286
and the other foreign embassies
to locate and identify

1013
01:33:49,323 --> 01:33:52,053
as many bodies as we can
as quickly as possible,

1014
01:33:52,093 --> 01:33:55,995
and to repatriate people,
either to medevac...

1015
01:33:57,531 --> 01:34:00,125
...commercial flights
to get home as soon as possible.

